<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-17T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-17T15:00:00-05:00" n="99" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d99">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/450: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-17T16:00:00-04:00">August 17,
                                    1935—4 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>216. Further reference your 359, August 9, 7 p.m. We are wondering
                            whether, in seeking qualitative limitation even without quantitative
                            limitation, the British have obtained information to the effect that the
                            Japanese have modified their position expressed last year that they
                            could not agree to qualitative without quantitative limitation.<note n="52" xml:id="d99fn52">See memorandum of conversation in the Prime
                                Minister’s office, November 23, 1934, <ref target="frus1934v01#pg_368">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1934, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 368</ref>.</note> We have no
                            word which would indicate that the Japanese have receded from this
                            position. Please endeavor to ascertain whether there has been any change
                            in this respect.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>